OL,6,F"Under the Online Safety Act, services
OL,7,Fmust take action to prevent users from
OL,8,Faccessing illegal suicide and self-
OL,9,Fharm content and ensure children are
OL,10,Fprotected from harmful content that
OL,11,Fpromotes it. If they fail to do so,
OL,12,Fthey can expect to face robust
OL,13,Fenforcement, including substantial
OL,14,Ffines.
